biz/claire-byrne-leaves-her-shed-as-she-returns-to-rte-studio|title=Back from the shed! Claire Byrnes returns to RT\u00c9 Studio|website=evoke.ie|first=Claire|last=Concannon|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n| [[Bray, County Wicklow|Bray]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.ie/regionals/braypeople/news/claire-byrne-live-from-her-home-shed-39052632.html|title=Claire Byrne Live from her home shed|work=[[Bray People]]|date=21 March 2020|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|\n| 1975\n| Journalist, presenter\n| Female\n|-\n|{{hs|Prendergast, Mark}}[[Kodaline|Mark Prendergast]]\n| Self-isolation<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.breakingnews.ie/showbiz/kodaline-guitarist-mark-prendergast-reveals-coronavirus-diagnosis-989757.html|title=Kodaline guitarist Mark Prendergast reveals coronavirus diagnosis|work=BreakingNews.ie|date=24 March 2020|quote=Prendergast said he took paracetamol, which helped, and drank around five litres of water a day. At one point, after several days on the sofa, he went for a run but it was a 'terrible idea'. He had to 'lie on the couch for two hours and could feel this tightness in my chest'. Prendergast added: 'I haven\u2019t seen my dad since March 12'.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.irishmirror.ie/showbiz/irish-showbiz/mark-prendergast-kodaline-coronavirus-covid-21745340|title=Coronavirus Ireland: Kodaline guitarist Mark Prendergast urges public to be 'over cautious' as he tests positive for Covid-19|work=Mirror|first=Katie|last=Gallagher|date=24 March 2020|quote=The guitarist, who used the Croke Park drive through facility to be tested believes he caught the virus while travelling through Heathrow Airport.}}</ref>\n| {{N/A}}\n| [[Swords, Dublin|Swords]]\n| Travel through [[Heathrow Airport]] (suspected)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rte.ie/entertainment/2020/0324/1125038-kodaline-guitarist-tests-positive-for-covid-19/|title=Kodaline guitarist tests positive for Covid-19|work=RT\u00c9 News|date=24 March 2020}}</r