ll National Football League draft picks|selected first overall]] by the [[Cincinnati Bengals]].<ref>{{cite web |author1=Around The NFL staff |title=58 prospects to virtually participate in NFL draft |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001108866/article/58-prospects-to-virtually-participate-in-nfl-draft |website=NFL.com |accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Baby |first1=Ben |title=Cincinnati Bengals take Joe Burrow with No. 1 pick in NFL draft |url=https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/29089822/cincinnati-bengals-take-joe-burrow-no-1-pick-nfl-draft |website=ESPN |accessdate=24 April 2020}}</ref> Burrow was the third consecutive Heisman Trophy\u2013winning quarterback, after [[Baker Mayfield]] and [[Kyler Murray]], to be selected first overall in the draft.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://247sports.com/Article/Joe-Burrow-Bengals-select-LSU-quarterback-with-first-pick-of-2020-NFL-Draft-146282738/|title=Joe Burrow drafted No. 1 overall by Bengals in 2020 NFL Draft|first=Dean|last=Straka|date=April 23, 2020|website=247Sports.com}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{Twitter}}\n*[http://www.lsusports.net/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=5200&ATCLID=211716545 LSU Tigers bio]\n*[https://www.bengals.com/team/players-roster/joe-burrow/ Cincinnati Bengals bio]\n\n{{Cincinnati Bengals roster navbox}}\n{{Navboxes|title=Joe Burrow\u2014awards, championships, and honors|list=\n{{LSU Tigers quarterback navbox}}\n{{2019 LSU Tigers football navbox}}\n{{Heisman Trophy}}\n{{Maxwell Award}}\n{{Walter Camp Award}}\n{{AP College Football Player of the Year}}\n{{Sporting News College Football Player of the Year}}\n{{2019 NCAA Division I FBS College Football Consensus All-Americans}}\n{{Davey O'Brien Award}}\n{{Johnny Unitas Award}}\n{{Manning Award}}\n{{Southeastern Conference Football Player of the Year navbox}}\n{{NCAA major college football passing yardage leaders}}\n{{NFL Number One Draft Picks}}\n{{2020 NFL Draft}}\n{{Bengal