{"title_page": "The Baltic Times", "text_new": "{{Infobox newspaper\n| name                = The Baltic Times\n| logo                = File:The_Baltic_Times_header.png\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| type                = Monthly [[newspaper]]\n| format              = \n| foundation          = 1996\n| ceased publication  =\n| political =\n| price               = \n| owners              = \n| political position  = \n| publisher           = \n| editor              = \n| staff               = \n| circulation         = \n| headquarters        = [[Riga]]\n| ISSN                = 1407-2300\n| oclc                = \n| website             = {{URL|http://www.baltictimes.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Baltic Times''''' is an independent monthly newspaper that covers the latest political, economic, business, and cultural events in [[Estonia]], [[Latvia]] and [[Lithuania]].<ref>[http://zefys.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/web/resource/details/8320/The%2BBaltic%2BTimes/ The Baltic Times] zefys.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de, retrieved 24 April 2020 (de/en)</ref>\n\nThe paper was formed from a merger in 1996 of the ''Baltic Independent'' and ''Baltic Observer''. With offices in [[Tallinn]] and [[Vilnius]] and its headquarters in [[Riga]], ''The Baltic Times'' remains the only [[English language]] print and online newspaper covering all three [[Baltic states]].\n\nBetween 1996 and 2012 ''The Baltic Times'' was published weekly and then, until September 2013, twice a month.<ref>[http://www.baltictimes.com ''About The Baltic Times''] Official website</ref>  \n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.baltictimes.com The Baltic Times]\n* [https://www.loc.gov/item/2010218073/ Library of Congress]\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Baltic Times, The}}\n[[Category:Newspapers published in Estonia]]\n[[Category:Newspapers published in Latvia]]\n[[Category:Newspapers published in Lithuania]]\n[[Category:Publications established in 1996]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Riga]]\n[[Category:Media in Riga]]\n[[Category:1996 establishments in Latvia]]\n[[Category:Latvian news websites]]\n\n{{latvia-newspaper-stub}}\n{{estonia-newspaper-stub}}\n{{lithuania-newspaper-stub}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=February 2012}}\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=November 2017}}\n{{Infobox newspaper\n| name                = The Baltic Times\n| logo                = File:The_Baltic_Times_header.png\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| type                = Monthly [[newspaper]]\n| format              = \n| foundation          = 1996\n| ceased publication  =\n| political =\n| price               = \n| owners              = \n| political position  = \n| publisher           = \n| editor              = \n| staff               = \n| circulation         = \n| headquarters        = [[Riga]]\n| ISSN                = 1407-2300\n| oclc                = \n| website             = {{URL|http://www.baltictimes.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Baltic Times''''' is an independent monthly newspaper that covers the latest political, economic, business, and cultural events in [[Estonia]], [[Latvia]] and [[Lithuania]].\n\nThe paper was formed from a merger in 1996 of the ''Baltic Independent'' and ''Baltic Observer''. With offices in [[Tallinn]] and [[Vilnius]] and its headquarters in [[Riga]], ''The Baltic Times'' remains the only [[English language]] print and online newspaper covering all three [[Baltic states]].\n\nBetween 1996 and 2012 ''The Baltic Times'' was published weekly and then, until September 2013, twice a month.<ref>[http://www.baltictimes.com ''About The Baltic Times''] Official website</ref>  \n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.baltictimes.com The Baltic Times]\n* [https://www.loc.gov/item/2010218073/ Library of Congress]\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Baltic Times, The}}\n[[Category:Newspapers published in Estonia]]\n[[Category:Newspapers published in Latvia]]\n[[Category:Newspapers published in Lithuania]]\n[[Category:Publications established in 1996]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Riga]]\n[[Category:Media in Riga]]\n[[Category:1996 establishments in Latvia]]\n[[Category:Latvian news websites]]\n\n{{latvia-newspaper-stub}}\n{{estonia-newspaper-stub}}\n{{lithuania-newspaper-stub}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=February 2012}}\n", "name_user": "Aguacatala", "label": "safe", "comment": "reference added", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Baltic_Times"}
